OVERVIEW:

 Project connects to my database and inserts, update, deletes, and selects data 
 from the database that corresponds to items and orders. Using the commands you
 can create a table of available items including information about them such as
 price, description and even amount available. Once you have items created you
 can create orders for those items. This program is design to not allow an order
 for an item that is not defined on the items table.
 


INCLUDED FILES:

 * Project.java - Driver class
 * MYSQLDatabase.java - Sets up database connection
 * Item.java - Object to hold reference to row of items table
 * Order.java - Object to hold reference to a row of orders table
 * SQL Procedure files
 *	-create_items_table.sql
 *  -create_ordres_table.sql
 * README - this file


COMPILING AND RUNNING:
 From the directory containing all source files, compile the
driver class (and all dependencies) with the command:
 $ javac Project.java

 Run the compiled class file with the command options:
 $ java Project CreateItem <itemCode> <itemDescription> <price> <inventory_amount>
 $ java Project UpdateInventory <item_code> < inventory_amount>
 $ java Project DeleteItem <item_code>
 $ java Project GetItems <item_code or % for all>
 $ java Project CreateOrder <item_code> <quantity>
 $ java Project DeleteOrder <item_code>
 $ java Project GetOrders <item_code or % for all>
 $ java Project GetOrderDetails <order_id or % for all>


 Console output will give the results of commands.